42
00:01:41,568 --> 00:01:45,272 line:-1
if there is no high-speed
Internet or data is limited?


43
00:01:45.272 --> 00:01:47.441 line:-1 position:50%
Or, will your app be welcoming


44
00:01:47.441 --> 00:01:50.577 line:-1 position:50%
for people across the spectrum
of gender identities


45
00:01:50,577 --> 00:01:54,348 line:-1
and LGBTQ+ communities?


46
00:01:54,348 --> 00:01:55,816 line:-1
As you view your app or game


47
00:01:55.816 --> 00:01:57.651 line:-1 position:50%
through many
different perspectives,


48
00:01:57,651 --> 00:02:00,554 line:-1
inclusiveness is about
making people feel welcome


49
00:02:00.554 --> 00:02:02.189 line:-1 position:50%
and considered.


50
00:02:02.189 --> 00:02:03.790 line:-1 position:50%
People who use it should feel


51
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:07,694 line:-1
that you designed with their
life experiences in mind.


52
00:02:07,694 --> 00:02:10,497 line:-1
Because your app can be used
by people around the world,


53
00:02:10,497 --> 00:02:13,867 line:-1
it lends to celebrating
humanity and difference.


54
00:02:13,867 --> 00:02:16,737 line:-1
Today, we will discuss how
creating apps or games


55
00:02:16.737 --> 00:02:18.271 line:-1 position:50%
for a diverse set of people


56
00:02:18.271 --> 00:02:22.275 line:-1 position:50%
requires inclusivity to be
infused into how you work


57
00:02:22,275 --> 00:02:25,379 line:-1
just as much
as what you choose to make.


58
00:02:25.379 --> 00:02:27.147 line:-1 position:50%
Before we dive into specifics,


59
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:29,816 line:-1
I will talk through
some common misconceptions


60
00:02:29,816 --> 00:02:32,019 line:-1
around inclusive design
and development


61
00:02:32,019 --> 00:02:34,354 line:-1
and how you can
think differently.


62
00:02:34.354 --> 00:02:37.691 line:-1 position:50%
At first, it may feel
like inclusion is hard.


63
00:02:37,691 --> 00:02:41,461 line:-1
But I would like to reframe this
as, "Inclusion is a journey."


64
00:02:41,461 --> 00:02:42,729 line:-1
Lots of things are hard,


65
00:02:42.729 --> 00:02:45.665 line:-1 position:50%
but we do them anyway
when they’re worthwhile.


66
00:02:45,665 --> 00:02:48,835 line:-1
Change is an iterative process
and takes time.


67
00:02:48,835 --> 00:02:51,738 line:-1
Meaningful change requires
planning, persistence,


68
00:02:51.738 --> 00:02:53.273 line:-1 position:50%
and patience.


69
00:02:53,273 --> 00:02:56,943 line:-1
The benefits are high, because
you can improve quality of life,


70
00:02:56,943 --> 00:03:01,448 line:-1
enable people to achieve
new goals, or try new things.


71
00:03:01,448 --> 00:03:02,649 line:-1
Another misconception


72
00:03:02.649 --> 00:03:05.652 line:-1 position:50%
is that inclusive design
limits creativity.


73
00:03:05,652 --> 00:03:08,188 line:-1
In truth, inclusive design
and development


74
00:03:08.188 --> 00:03:10.957 line:-1 position:50%
stimulates new
creative solutions.


75
00:03:10,957 --> 00:03:14,594 line:-1
Wider context and awareness
can promote progress in areas


76
00:03:14,594 --> 00:03:17,197 line:-1
that you may have
never considered before.


77
00:03:17,197 --> 00:03:20,033 line:-1
You can make breakthroughs
in experiences for everyone


78
00:03:20.033 --> 00:03:22.069 line:-1 position:50%
that wouldn’t happen
if you didn’t consider


79
00:03:22.069 --> 00:03:24.905 line:-1 position:50%
the diversity
of human experience.


80
00:03:24,905 --> 00:03:27,641 line:-1
Inclusion doesn’t mean
turning down innovative ideas


81
00:03:27.641 --> 00:03:29.109 line:-1 position:50%
or asking all people to accept


82
00:03:29,109 --> 00:03:31,845 line:-1
a lowest common denominator
experience.


83
00:03:31,845 --> 00:03:33,447 line:-1
Constraints help your process


84
00:03:33,447 --> 00:03:36,283 line:-1
by helping you make
the first few early decisions.


85
00:03:36,283 --> 00:03:38,285 line:-1
This allows you to put
most of your energy


86
00:03:38,285 --> 00:03:41,855 line:-1
into creating new solutions
in a narrow problem space.


87
00:03:41.855 --> 00:03:43.590 line:-1 position:50%
Let me share
an example with you.


88
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:46,593 line:-1
A team at Apple figured out how
they can use our Apple products


89
00:03:46,593 --> 00:03:49,729 line:-1
to add a layer of intelligence
to our physical world.


90
00:03:49.729 --> 00:03:51.298 line:-1 position:50%
They first wanted to focus


91
00:03:51,298 --> 00:03:53,733 line:-1
on recognizing
a few objects and text,


92
00:03:53.733 --> 00:03:55.836 line:-1 position:50%
which in itself is a constraint.


93
00:03:55,836 --> 00:03:57,871 line:0
But they didn’t just stop there.


94
00:03:57,871 --> 00:04:01,541 line:0
They explored ways to surface
buttons to call, message,


95
00:04:01,541 --> 00:04:05,212 line:0
add to contacts, or copy
recognized phone numbers.


96
00:04:05,212 --> 00:04:06,480 line:0
It’s helpful to me


97
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:09,182 position:50%
but essential for people
who are blind or low vision


98
00:04:09,182 --> 00:04:11,818 line:0
to interact with printed
materials like signs,


99
00:04:11,818 --> 00:04:13,720 line:0
business cards, and envelopes.


100
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:16,490 line:0
Not only can people
who are blind read this text,


101
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:20,193 line:0
they can act on it to make calls
and save contacts.


102
00:04:20,193 --> 00:04:23,763 position:50%
This brings us to
a misconception about teams.


103
00:04:23.763 --> 00:04:25.632 line:-1 position:50%
You may think
that having a diverse team


104
00:04:25.632 --> 00:04:28.368 line:-1 position:50%
means your app or game
will be inclusive.


105
00:04:28,368 --> 00:04:32,005 line:-1
In truth, having an empowered
diverse team


106
00:04:32,005 --> 00:04:35,142 line:-1
means your app
or game can be inclusive.


107
00:04:35,142 --> 00:04:37,444 line:-1
We all share
the responsibility to build


108
00:04:37,444 --> 00:04:41,615 line:-1
an inclusive environment
that enables inclusive actions.


109
00:04:41,615 --> 00:04:43,817 line:-1
You’re more engaged
when you feel comfortable


110
00:04:43,817 --> 00:04:45,719 line:-1
voicing your ideas and opinions.


111
00:04:45,719 --> 00:04:48,688 line:-1
And when those thoughts come
from a diverse group of people,


112
00:04:48,688 --> 00:04:52,559 line:-1
it fosters more creativity
and innovation.


113
00:04:52.559 --> 00:04:55.362 line:-1 position:50%
At Apple, the accessibility
engineers work hand in hand


114
00:04:55,362 --> 00:04:58,598 line:-1
with a wide array of teams
to help solve unique problems


115
00:04:58,598 --> 00:05:01,401 line:-1
that affect only
a certain group of people.


116
00:05:01,401 --> 00:05:04,337 line:-1
For example, a person
who is blind or has low vision


117
00:05:04.337 --> 00:05:07.541 line:-1 position:50%
might have difficulty knowing
when to move forward in a line


118
00:05:07,541 --> 00:05:09,176 line:-1
independently.


119
00:05:09,176 --> 00:05:11,912 line:-1
A solution started with
the video engineering team


120
00:05:11.912 --> 00:05:14.748 line:-1 position:50%
using the technology
called "LiDAR."


121
00:05:14.748 --> 00:05:18.084 line:-1 position:50%
It uses a pulsed laser
to ping nearby objects


122
00:05:18,084 --> 00:05:21,955 line:-1
to generate a 3D model
of the surrounding environment.


123
00:05:21.955 --> 00:05:24.591 line:-1 position:50%
The teams were empowered
to work together


124
00:05:24,591 --> 00:05:27,694 line:-1
to create and release
the People Detection feature


125
00:05:27.694 --> 00:05:29.496 line:-1 position:50%
in the Magnifier app.


126
00:05:29,496 --> 00:05:31,865 position:50%
It allows you to know
the distance between you


127
00:05:31,865 --> 00:05:34,568 line:0
and the people around you.


128
00:05:34,568 --> 00:05:37,137 line:0
What started as a prototype
to make life more convenient


129
00:05:37,137 --> 00:05:39,839 position:50%
became a necessity
once COVID-19 hit.


130
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:43,143 position:50%
Our team's ongoing conversations
with the blind community


131
00:05:43,143 --> 00:05:45,178 position:50%
led to a more pressing issue:


132
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:47,314 line:0
How does a blind
or low-vision person


133
00:05:47,314 --> 00:05:50,784 position:50%
practice social distancing?


134
00:05:50.784 --> 00:05:51.952 line:-1 position:50%
One more misconception


135
00:05:51,952 --> 00:05:55,088 line:-1
is that inclusion
can be done at the very end.


136
00:05:55.088 --> 00:05:57.257 line:-1 position:50%
Considering inclusion
and the experience


137
00:05:57,257 --> 00:06:00,360 line:-1
that each individual person --
or groups of people --


138
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:03,830 line:-1
have with your app or game
must be considered upfront


139
00:06:03,830 --> 00:06:07,267 line:-1
and carried throughout
the design and development.


140
00:06:07,267 --> 00:06:09,569 line:-1
Waiting until the end
is reactionary,


141
00:06:09,569 --> 00:06:12,739 line:-1
and there often isn’t
enough time to correct.


142
00:06:12,739 --> 00:06:15,542 line:-1
More than small changes
become risky.


143
00:06:15.542 --> 00:06:18.044 line:-1 position:50%
This doesn’t mean you have
to get it right from the start,


144
00:06:18,044 --> 00:06:20,580 line:-1
but that it's being considered
from the start.


145
00:06:20.580 --> 00:06:23.083 line:-1 position:50%
Now we can build
on these reframings


146
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:26,987 line:-1
to empower us to create
more inclusive apps or games.


147
00:06:26.987 --> 00:06:30.724 line:-1 position:50%
To start, you can take
a deeper look into how you work.


148
00:06:30.724 --> 00:06:33.927 line:-1 position:50%
You can be in a better position
to achieve your inclusion goals


149
00:06:33,927 --> 00:06:37,364 line:-1
if you first look
at the diversity of your teams


150
00:06:37,364 --> 00:06:41,167 line:-1
in creating inclusive
working environments.


151
00:06:41,167 --> 00:06:44,371 line:-1
At Apple, we believe our teams
should reflect the diverse,


152
00:06:44,371 --> 00:06:46,740 line:-1
ever-evolving world we serve.


153
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:48,808 line:-1
People are drawn
to like-mindedness,


154
00:06:48.808 --> 00:06:50.710 line:-1 position:50%
consensus, and agreement.


155
00:06:50,710 --> 00:06:53,680 line:-1
It feels comfortable
and takes less mental energy,


156
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:56,916 line:-1
but it doesn’t always
get you the best results.


157
00:06:56,916 --> 00:06:58,852 line:-1
When you see difference
as an asset,


158
00:06:58.852 --> 00:07:00.253 line:-1 position:50%
rather than a challenge,


159
00:07:00.253 --> 00:07:02.756 line:-1 position:50%
you open yourself
to new possibilities,


160
00:07:02.756 --> 00:07:06.159 line:-1 position:50%
creative thinking, and
productive new relationships


161
00:07:06,159 --> 00:07:09,329 line:-1
that help you
make better decisions.


162
00:07:09,329 --> 00:07:11,931 line:-1
In some ways, small companies
are better positioned


163
00:07:11.931 --> 00:07:13.600 line:-1 position:50%
to build more inclusive teams


164
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:16,336 line:-1
if you commit
to diversity early.


165
00:07:16,336 --> 00:07:18,405 line:-1
People tend to hire
those they know,


166
00:07:18.405 --> 00:07:19.439 line:-1 position:50%
which poses the risk


167
00:07:19.439 --> 00:07:22.208 line:-1 position:50%
of them having
very similar perspectives.


168
00:07:22.208 --> 00:07:24.644 line:-1 position:50%
If you instead bring on
someone different from you,


169
00:07:24.644 --> 00:07:28.081 line:-1 position:50%
you have an easier path
to making diversity a core value


170
00:07:28,081 --> 00:07:31,851 line:-1
from the get-go rather
than rushing to fix it later on.


171
00:07:31,851 --> 00:07:34,888 line:-1
And as you grow your teams,
think “culture add,”


172
00:07:34.888 --> 00:07:36.623 line:-1 position:50%
rather than “culture fit.”


173
00:07:36.623 --> 00:07:38.458 line:-1 position:50%
What perspectives
are you missing


174
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:40,660 line:-1
and how could finding
that perspective


175
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:43,129 line:-1
change your app for the better?


176
00:07:43,129 --> 00:07:44,564 line:-1
Your team can be diverse,


177
00:07:44,564 --> 00:07:46,700 line:-1
but it’s often
that diverse perspectives


178
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:49,169 line:-1
are not incorporated
in meaningful ways


179
00:07:49.169 --> 00:07:52.205 line:-1 position:50%
that impact decision making.


180
00:07:52,205 --> 00:07:54,941 line:-1
You want to make sure
you are actively creating space


181
00:07:54,941 --> 00:07:58,845 line:-1
and asking for perspectives
in a judgment-free way.


182
00:07:58.845 --> 00:08:00.447 line:-1 position:50%
To create safe spaces,


183
00:08:00.447 --> 00:08:04.217 line:-1 position:50%
teams need time and space
to think inclusively.


184
00:08:04.217 --> 00:08:05.885 line:-1 position:50%
Protect this time.


185
00:08:05.885 --> 00:08:08.421 line:-1 position:50%
The design and development
process can be rigid


186
00:08:08.421 --> 00:08:09.456 line:-1 position:50%
and unwavering,


187
00:08:09.456 --> 00:08:12.192 line:-1 position:50%
so much so that you don’t feel
like you can take time


188
00:08:12,192 --> 00:08:15,562 line:-1
to reflect and think about
what you are making.


189
00:08:15.562 --> 00:08:17.597 line:-1 position:50%
Fast development
also doesn’t allow you


190
00:08:17,597 --> 00:08:21,768 line:-1
to incorporate the diverse
perspectives from your teams.


191
00:08:21,768 --> 00:08:24,637 line:-1
Now we will look at the design
and development process


192
00:08:24,637 --> 00:08:27,040 line:-1
more closely, and I will share
tips and pointers


193
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:28,942 line:-1
to consider during each phase.


194
00:08:28.942 --> 00:08:31.211 line:-1 position:50%
If you were to illustrate
the process,


195
00:08:31,211 --> 00:08:33,246 line:-1
you may first think of it
as a line


196
00:08:33.246 --> 00:08:35.915 line:-1 position:50%
with point A
of formulating the idea


197
00:08:35.915 --> 00:08:38.118 line:-1 position:50%
to point B of releasing.


198
00:08:38.118 --> 00:08:39.853 line:-1 position:50%
In the middle
are lengths for phases


199
00:08:39,853 --> 00:08:43,590 line:-1
like design, development,
and testing.


200
00:08:43.590 --> 00:08:45.358 line:-1 position:50%
Much like security or privacy,


201
00:08:45,358 --> 00:08:48,261 line:-1
inclusion cannot be treated
as an afterthought.


202
00:08:48,261 --> 00:08:50,463 line:-1
Since you don’t want
to release your app or game


203
00:08:50.463 --> 00:08:53.099 line:-1 position:50%
and discover that it doesn’t
work well for everyone,


204
00:08:53.099 --> 00:08:55.869 line:-1 position:50%
you can dedicate
and reserve time to pause,


205
00:08:55.869 --> 00:08:58.605 line:-1 position:50%
think, and pivot throughout
the whole process,


206
00:08:58.605 --> 00:09:00.974 line:-1 position:50%
not just at the end.


207
00:09:00,974 --> 00:09:04,944 line:-1
It really becomes a
rejuvenating, iterative process.


208
00:09:04,944 --> 00:09:07,647 line:-1
Taking time out of each phase
to reflect,


209
00:09:07,647 --> 00:09:09,015 line:-1
ask some key questions,


210
00:09:09.015 --> 00:09:12.619 line:-1 position:50%
can be helpful to evaluate
what you are making.


211
00:09:12,619 --> 00:09:15,188 line:-1
It may feel like you are
looping back momentarily,


212
00:09:15,188 --> 00:09:17,624 line:-1
but the new, more inclusive path
will ultimately


213
00:09:17.624 --> 00:09:20.527 line:-1 position:50%
make the app or game
relate to more people.


214
00:09:20,527 --> 00:09:21,895 line:-1
It will also give you more time


215
00:09:21,895 --> 00:09:23,897 line:-1
to tackle things
that may be complex


216
00:09:23.897 --> 00:09:27.167 line:-1 position:50%
and require longer time
to solve.


217
00:09:27,167 --> 00:09:29,502 line:-1
Now we will discuss
what you can ask yourself


218
00:09:29,502 --> 00:09:32,372 line:-1
or do during each phase.


219
00:09:32.372 --> 00:09:34.441 line:-1 position:50%
First, we’ll start
when you ideate


220
00:09:34.441 --> 00:09:36.443 line:-1 position:50%
on what you are going to make.


221
00:09:36.443 --> 00:09:38.011 line:-1 position:50%
Everyone working
on the app or game


222
00:09:38,011 --> 00:09:40,280 line:-1
should be able
to answer the question:


223
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:44,150 line:-1
Why are you making this?
Will everyone relate to it?


