360
00:16:01.093 --> 00:16:05.298 line:-1 position:50%
So our team needed to understand
how the image descriptions model


361
00:16:05.298 --> 00:16:08.968 line:-1 position:50%
described all people,
not just average people.


362
00:16:08,968 --> 00:16:09,802 line:-1
If you’re working on


363
00:16:09,802 --> 00:16:12,004 line:-1
machine-learning-powered
features,


364
00:16:12,004 --> 00:16:15,441 line:-1
one place to start is to learn
how different groups of people


365
00:16:15.441 --> 00:16:17.810 line:-1 position:50%
are represented
by machine learning.


366
00:16:17.810 --> 00:16:20.213 line:-1 position:50%
And this is a step
