408
00:18:14,593 --> 00:18:18,264 line:-1
and who are part
of the LGBTQ+ community,


409
00:18:18.264 --> 00:18:22.368 line:-1 position:50%
which is inclusive of non-binary
and transgender people.


410
00:18:22.368 --> 00:18:25.137 line:-1 position:50%
Our team learned that you can’t
know someone’s gender


411
00:18:25,137 --> 00:18:27,039 line:-1
by looking at a photo.


412
00:18:27.039 --> 00:18:28.040 line:-1 position:50%
We also learned


413
00:18:28.040 --> 00:18:30.276 line:-1 position:50%
that gender-neutral
image descriptions


414
00:18:30.276 --> 00:18:33.079 line:-1 position:50%
could still provide
helpful details


415
00:18:33.079 --> 00:18:35.114 line:-1 position:50%
by focusing on other things,


416
00:18:35.114 --> 00:18:38.017 line:-1 position:50%
such as people’s clothes
and hairstyles.


417
00:18:38,017 --> 00:18:42,555 line:-1
For now, we developed VoiceOver
Recognition image descriptions


418
00:18:42,555 --> 00:18:44,390 line:-1
to be gender neutral.


419
00:18:44,390 --> 00:18:46,425 line:-1
As an example, let’s hear


420
00:18:46.425 --> 00:18:50.329 line:-1 position:50%
the VoiceOver Recognition image
